2026-04-16 12:07:17 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['lamp (main bulb, load module)'] hypothesis_explanation='All upstream points, including the relay contacts and all cable and PCB connections up to the load module, show nominal voltage and continuity. At the input of the load module, the voltage is unusually low (~0.36 V) compared to the expected 12 V, and both the main and indicator bulbs are not receiving voltage or current, indicating a possible internal open circuit at the entry to or within the lamp circuit itself. This could be caused by a partially failed or intermittently open main bulb, possibly with a failed filament that makes momentary contact. The symptoms (lamp cycling off and on, no current through the diode when off, no voltage to the indicator) support an open or faulty main bulb.'
