description: Monitor the voltage at the output of the light sensor (the node controlling the relay driver circuit) over time—particularly during the seconds when the lamp turns off—to verify if the control signal to the relay is fluctuating every 20 seconds, possibly triggering the relay to open or change state., outcome='The measured voltage at the output of the ambient light sensor is 0.119 V relative to ground (with a negative side at 0.0003 V). No unexpected voltage fluctuations or polarity inversions were observed in this measurement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> lamp module diode,
description: Test the lamp module diode by measuring the voltage drop across it during normal operation and specifically during the lamp's periodic off interval. Check if the diode is intermittently blocking current, causing the lamp to turn off., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened, and the diode forward voltage test shows a nominal value (Vf = 0.7 V expected and measured). Voltage readings across the diode during normal operation indicate approximately 0.36 V on the anode and near zero on the cathode, but the current through the diode is 0.0 A, indicating no current flow through the diode at this time. No polarity inversion was detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_diode', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> lamp indicator (small bulb in load module),
description: Test the lamp indicator (the small parallel bulb to the main lamp) during both the on and off intervals of the main lamp. Measure voltage and observe whether it is turning off with the main lamp or remains on, to determine if the load circuit is being completely disconnected or if only the main lamp is affected., outcome='The measured voltage across the Internal Indicator Lamp is effectively zero (0.0003 V), and the lamp is not lit. This indicates there is no significant voltage present at the lamp terminals and the parallel branch is fully de-energized.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched cable terminals (between Control and Load modules),
description: Measure the voltage at the output terminals of the control module (switched cables toward the load module) during both on and off intervals of the lamp to confirm if voltage is being supplied to the load module at all times, or if there is an intermittent supply loss., outcome='The measured voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, while the Control Output Cable (−) shows 0.0003 V relative to ground. No polarity inversion is detected in the measured cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> cable connections between Control and Load modules,
description: Visually inspect the cable and terminal connections between the Control module and the Load module for signs of loose, intermittent, or faulty connections that could cause voltage drops or disconnects. Pay close attention to the polarity and physical contact quality., outcome='All cables observed have no visible internal faults, and all relevant connections are confirmed. No issues with loose, intermittent, or faulty connections were identified during visual inspection. No POLARITY INVERSION detected in current cable and terminal arrangement.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply module (battery output terminals),
description: Measure the voltage directly at the battery terminals (inside the power supply module) during both on and off lamp intervals to confirm if battery voltage is stable or if it is intermittently dropping, possibly due to an internal or contact issue in the battery case., outcome='Voltage measured at the battery terminals is 12.0 V (positive terminal) and 0.0 V (negative terminal) with respect to ground. No instability or voltage drop at the battery terminals is indicated.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=30.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module internal circuit (relay driver / logic circuit),
description: Monitor the output of the relay driver circuit (the circuit node that directly energizes the relay coil) over multiple lamp cycles to verify whether the relay driver is being triggered off periodically, resulting in loss of voltage at the output terminals., outcome="Voltage at the 'Control Relay' was measured as 11.9873 V on the positive terminal and 0.3592 V on the negative terminal with respect to ground. No polarity inversion was detected at this step. The inspection panel is open and measurements were successfully taken.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=25.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched contacts (output of relay, during lamp OFF period),
description: Directly measure continuity across the relay's switched contacts during the lamp OFF interval to confirm if the relay contacts are opening (disconnecting load) or if they remain closed with loss of output voltage. This will clarify if the relay itself is malfunctioning intermittently despite stable control signals., outcome="Continuity measurement across the relay's switched contacts during the lamp OFF interval is nominal, with resistance measured at 0.01 Ω, matching the nominal value. The relay contacts remain closed during this period.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> switched input cables between power supply and control module,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of the control module (where it receives 12V from the power supply) during both the lamp ON and OFF intervals to check for a voltage drop or intermittent disconnection upstream of the control module., outcome="The voltage at 'Control Input Cable (+)' is 11.99 V, and at 'Control Input Cable (−)' is approximately 0 V, both referenced to ground. No polarity inversion is detected in the measured connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.", precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> internal wiring/PCB traces (control module, load module),
description: Perform continuity and voltage checks along the internal wiring and PCB traces that lead from the switched output terminals in the control module to the lamp terminals in the load module, checking for an open, high-resistance, or intermittent internal trace or joint that is not externally visible., outcome='Continuity checks between the control output cables and the corresponding load input cables are good, with low resistance (0.1 Ω) and no open or high-resistance joints found. Voltage at the load input (+) terminal is 0.3592 V, while all other points—including both terminals of the main and internal bulbs—are at 0.0003 V. No polarity inversion is detected in these connections.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=145.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> diode (load module),
description: Perform a detailed visual inspection of the load module diode to check for any signs of intermittent physical issues such as overheating, solder cracks, loose mounting, or damage that could cause sporadic blocking of current., outcome='The inspection panel was successfully opened, and the Load Protection Diode was visually inspected. No observable internal faults were detected on the diode.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=15.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> lamp module (both bulbs, disconnected from circuit),
description: Test both the main lamp and the indicator lamp in the load module by applying a known external voltage (e.g., 12V from a bench power supply or battery) directly across each bulb, after disconnecting them from the circuit, to determine if either bulb displays intermittent or abnormal behavior under a stable supply., outcome='Both the main lamp and the indicator lamp show nominal resistance values when measured with a multimeter, indicating normal continuity. No abnormalities were detected in either bulb during this test.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Power supply module indicator circuit (green LED branch resistor),
description: Test the LED indicator branch resistor in the power supply module for a partial or high-resistance failure that could cause the indicator LED to light normally while not delivering full current to the circuit. Measure the voltage across and current through the resistor, and check continuity to confirm it is not introducing an unwanted series resistance to the supply line., outcome='The PSU Green LED Resistor measurements indicate a voltage drop from 11.99 V to 1.29 V, a branch current of 10.7 mA, and a measured resistance of 1000 Ω matching the nominal value. Continuity is confirmed as nominal. No partial or high-resistance fault is detected in the resistor.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=70.0, cost_breakdown=[('invert_enclosure', 10.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> battery terminal and power supply module output terminals during lamp ON/OFF cycling,
description: Simultaneously monitor (preferably oscilloscope or fast-logging voltmeter) the voltage at the battery terminals and immediately at the power supply output terminals (feeding the control module) during the times when the lamp turns off and back on. This checks for fast, transient supply drops or voltage interruptions not detected by previous steady-state measurements., outcome='The battery voltage measures 12.0 V. The PSU Output Cable (+) is at approximately 11.99 V, while the PSU Output Cable (−) is at approximately 0 V. No polarity inversion is detected between the battery and PSU output cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=60.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> ambient sensor module (switched cables indicator LED branch),
description: Measure the voltage at both ends of the 'Switched Cables Indicator' LED branch in the control module—particularly during the intervals when the load lamp turns off—to check whether the LED is switching or dimming in sync with the main lamp's outage. This will clarify if the issue is caused by something within the sensor module relay switching, or by a downstream load-side issue., outcome='The Control Relay shows a voltage of approximately 12 V on its positive terminal and 0.36 V on its negative terminal. The Main Load lamp has near-zero voltage on both measured terminals. No polarity inversion was detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=65.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> power supply output cables (from PSU to control module),
description: Monitor the current in each power supply output cable leading from the PSU to the control module during operation, especially during lamp on-off cycles. This will check for possible intermittent series resistance, internal wire fracture, or poor crimp/terminal contact not visible during simple voltage or visual inspection, which might cause repeated voltage drops when load current is drawn., outcome='Both current measurements were successful. The PSU Output Cable (+) carries 0.001666 A, and the PSU Output Cable (−) carries -0.001666 A. No polarity inversion is detected.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_current', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
